The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	Calcutta: The Sri Lanka team and captain Kumar Sangakkara picked up fines for maintaining a slow over-rate in the second T20I at Mohali on Saturday. In accordance with the new ICC code of conduct, players are fined 10 per cent of their match fees for every over outside allotted time, with the captain fined double that amount. The Lankans were two overs short. Match Referee Jeff Crowe said: Under the revised code of conduct, Lanka was very close to being three overs behind which would have resulted in Sangakkara being suspended in the next two ODIs.        
	Pretoria: England cricketer Stuart Broad Monday said he will turn down offers to play in next years lucrative Indian Premier League (IPL) in order to be in peak form for the 2010 Ashes in Australia. Broads England teammate James Anderson, too, has made a similar announcement the ECB said on its website.         
	Calcutta: Cricket Australia Monday announced that Tasmanian pacer Brett Geeves will join the squad for the third Test vs the West Indies, that begins Wednesday. Geeves is coming in as cover for the injured Peter Siddle.      
	Younis move    
	Karachi: Former Pakistan captain Younis Khan began a coaching course at the national academy in Lahore on Monday after taking a break from international cricket last month.        
	Calcutta: Sania Mirza had improved her ranking by a spot to be at No.57 on the WTA singles chart released Monday. She was static at No.37 in doubles. Unchanged, too, were the ATP doubles rankings of Mahesh Bhupathi and Leander Paes, who were at No.7 and No.8 respectively. Somdev Dev Varman was holding on to his No.126 on the singles chart. Roger Federer continues to be the mens No.1 with Serena Williams leading the womens list.      
	NBA website  
	Mumbai: The National Basketball Association (NBA) Monday launched its official online and mobile sites designed for audiences in India. The website is accessible at www.nba.com/india.    
	Monaco: The IAAF has amended its results to list disgraced Greek sprinter Katerina Thanou as winner of the 100m at the 2000 Sydney Olympics.  
	Massa to drive				 				 																  
	 London: Felipe Massa will drive a Ferrari F1 car again this year as the Brazilian continues his recovery from life-threatening head injuries suffered in July, Ferrari said on Sunday.
        
	Kuala Lumpur: Italian Jarno Trulli and Finn Heikki Kovalainen will drive for Lotus in the 2010 Formula One season, the new Malaysian-backed team announced Monday. Lotus are one of four new teams entering the sport next season in an expanded 26 car starting grid.                                                                                                                                                      
